The paper focuses on the performance analysis of LiDAR-based SLAM for autonomous vehicles in diverse urban scenarios, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes LiDAR point clouds to perform mapping and positioning, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper employs state-of-the-art graph-based optimization to integrate LiDAR odometry measurements, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper aims to improve the reliability of autonomous driving, which is a significant application in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
